<font color="White">to help develop the concentration 
     span of airline pilots.</font>

00:15.879 --> 00:19.959
 After all, driving and flying    
       <font color="White">are very similar.</font>

00:19.959 --> 00:21.239
         <font color="White">In both cases,</font>

00:21.239 --> 00:24.439
    <font color="White">we need to concentrate        
   on several things at once</font>

00:24.439 --> 00:28.000
  so we need to decide what is    
<font color="White">most important to concentrate on</font>

00:28.000 --> 00:29.520
       <font color="White">at any given time.</font>

00:30.520 --> 00:32.239
  In the following exercises,

00:32.239 --> 00:36.680
<font color="White">you're going to practise performing
    two tasks at the same time.</font>

00:36.680 --> 00:40.360
  The first task is a bit like    
    <font color="White">driving in dense traffic</font>

00:40.360 --> 00:42.360
  at a reasonably high speed.

00:42.360 --> 00:45.760
    <font color="White">You'll have to maintain       
a safe distance between your car</font>

00:45.760 --> 00:47.520
     <font color="White">and the car in front.</font>

00:47.520 --> 00:50.119
       <font color="White">In the other task,         
  you'll have to use your eyes</font>

00:50.119 --> 00:51.520
  and your rear vision mirrors

00:51.520 --> 00:52.800
   <font color="White">to look at lots of numbers</font>

00:52.800 --> 00:56.879
 which will appear in different   
   <font color="White">locations around your car.</font>

00:56.879 --> 00:58.720
<font color="White">It's a bit like when you're driving</font>

00:58.720 --> 01:01.000
      <font color="White">and looking out for         
      potential hazards.</font>

01:01.000 --> 01:04.879
<font color="White">Each time you see a number, you'll
have to make a decision about it.</font>

01:06.400 --> 01:07.959
<font color="White">You're most probably wondering,</font>

01:07.959 --> 01:11.200
